## 🧠 SECTION 1 — THE IDEA

> What happens when nothing ends?

Stories depend on change.

On decisions.
On consequences.
On things that begin — and things that stop.

But what if they didn’t?

What if a character never disappeared?
What if a system never reset?
What if continuity replaced renewal?

Some structures can sustain themselves.

Others, when extended too far, begin to collapse.

